Get study data

  • strat: 0 -> aleatoric feedback, 1 -> epistemic feedback
  • first: order in which the condition was performed
  • acc_eval: Response to Likert-scale question of the questionnaire "My classifier has been well trained"
  • usefulness_knows : Response to Likert-scale question of the questionnaire "The uncertainty measure A helped me identify the examples that my classifier knows how to recognize."
  • usefulness_unknows : Response to Likert-scale question of the questionnaire "The uncertainty measure helped me identify examples that my classifier does not recognize."
  • usefulness_ambiguous: Response to Likert-scale question of the questionnaire "The uncertainty measure helped me identify ambiguous examples for my classifier."
  • test_acc: Score at the user accuracy test
  • test_uncert: Error at the user uncertainty test,
  • training_size: size of the training set

import seaborn as sns
import scipy
import matplotlib
sns.set_theme()


mapping = {"test_acc": "Classification test score", "test_uncert": "Uncertainty test score", "training_size": "Training set size", "intraclass_features": "Training set variability", "strat": "Type of uncertainty", "first": "Order"}
plot_data = all_data[["strat", "first", "training_size", "intraclass_features", "test_acc", "test_uncert"]].rename(columns = mapping)

plot_data["Type of uncertainty"] = plot_data["Type of uncertainty"].map({0: "Data uncertainty", 1: "Model uncertainty"})
plot_data["Order"] = plot_data["Order"].map({1: "First iteration", 2: "Second iteration"})

format = "line"

if format == "line":

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,4, figsize=(22,5))

    for ax in axes:
        for item in ([ax.title, ax.xaxis.label, ax.yaxis.label] +
                ax.get_xticklabels() + ax.get_yticklabels()):
            item.set_fontsize(20)

    # axes[0].set_xlim([0,100])

    sns.regplot(ax =axes[0], x="Training set size", y="Uncertainty test score", data=plot_data, color = "b")
    sns.regplot(ax =axes[2], x="Training set variability", y="Uncertainty test score", data=plot_data, color = "b")
    sns.regplot(ax =axes[1], x="Training set size", y="Classification test score", data=plot_data, color = "darkorange")
    sns.regplot(ax =axes[3], x="Training set variability", y="Classification test score", data=plot_data, color = "darkorange")

    # g = sns.pairplot(plot_data, x_vars=["Training set size", "Training set variability"], y_vars=["Uncertainty test score", "Classification test score"], palette = sns.color_palette("colorblind"), markers = "+")

    axes[0].set_xlim((np.min(plot_data["Training set size"])*(1-0.15),np.max(plot_data["Training set size"])*(1+0.05)))
    axes[1].set_xlim((np.min(plot_data["Training set size"])*(1-0.15),np.max(plot_data["Training set size"])*(1+0.05)))
    axes[2].set_xlim((np.min(plot_data["Training set variability"])*(1-0.05),np.max(plot_data["Training set variability"])*(1+0.025)))
    axes[3].set_xlim((np.min(plot_data["Training set variability"])*(1-0.05),np.max(plot_data["Training set variability"])*(1+0.025)))


    ax = axes[0]
    ax.axhline(y = 2/3, color = 'k', linestyle = '--')
    slope, intercept, r_value, p_value, std_err = scipy.stats.linregress(plot_data["Training set size"],plot_data["Uncertainty test score"])
    ax.text(20, 0.61,  "R = {0:.2f}".format(r_value) + "\n" + r'$p_{value}$' + "= {0:.3f}".format(p_value), fontsize=20)

    ax = axes[2]
    ax.axhline(y = 2/3, color = 'k', linestyle = '--')

    ax.text(16.5, 0.61,  "R = {0:.2f}".format(r_value) + "\n" + r'$p_{value}$' + "= {0:.3f}".format(p_value), fontsize=20)

ANOVA between groups on acc_test and uncert_test

In[136]:
## Acc_test and Uncert_test

# AB (aleatoric / epistemic)
print("--- AB ---")
selectionA = all_data.loc[all_data["strat"] == 0]
selectionB = all_data.loc[all_data["strat"] == 1]
print("Model accuracy:", stat.f_oneway(selectionA["accuracy"].values, selectionB["accuracy"].values))
print("Precision test:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["test_acc"].values, selectionB["test_acc"].values))
print("Uncertainty test:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["test_uncert"].values, selectionB["test_uncert"].values))
print("Variability:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["intraclass_features"].values, selectionB["intraclass_features"].values))
print("Training size:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["training_size"].values, selectionB["training_size"].values))


# Order (learning effect )
print("--- Order ---")
selectionA = all_data.loc[all_data["first"] == 1]
selectionB = all_data.loc[all_data["first"] == 2]
print("Model accuracy:", stat.f_oneway(selectionA["accuracy"].values, selectionB["accuracy"].values))
print("Precision test:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["test_acc"].values, selectionB["test_acc"].values))
print("Uncertainty test:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["test_uncert"].values, selectionB["test_uncert"].values))
print("Variability:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["intraclass_features"].values, selectionB["intraclass_features"].values))
print("Training size:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["training_size"].values, selectionB["training_size"].values))

# Systematicity quantitative
print("--- Systematic VS the rest ---")
selectionA = all_data.loc[all_data["systematic"] == 1]
selectionB = all_data.loc[all_data["systematic"] == 0]
print("Umbalanced groups: systematic:", len(selectionA), ", the rest: ", len(selectionB))
print("Model accuracy:", stat.f_oneway(selectionA["accuracy"].values, selectionB["accuracy"].values))
print("Precision test:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["test_acc"].values, selectionB["test_acc"].values))
print("Uncertainty test:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["test_uncert"].values, selectionB["test_uncert"].values))
print("Variability:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["intraclass_features"].values, selectionB["intraclass_features"].values))
print("Training size:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["training_size"].values, selectionB["training_size"].values))

# Uncertainty as guidance
print("--- Uncertainty as guidance VS the rest ---")
selectionA = all_data.loc[all_data["uncertainty_as_guidance"] == 1]
selectionB = all_data.loc[all_data["uncertainty_as_guidance"] == 0]
print("Umbalanced groups: uncertainty_as_guidance: ", len(selectionA), ", the rest: ", len(selectionB))
print("Model accuracy:", stat.f_oneway(selectionA["accuracy"].values, selectionB["accuracy"].values))
print("Precision test:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["test_acc"].values, selectionB["test_acc"].values))
print("Uncertainty test:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["test_uncert"].values, selectionB["test_uncert"].values))
print("Variability:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["intraclass_features"].values, selectionB["intraclass_features"].values))
print("Training size:",stat.f_oneway(selectionA["training_size"].values, selectionB["training_size"].values))

# Better than random for test_acc
print("--- Better than random for participant classification test  ---")

import random
group_control = []
for i in range(1000):
    group_control.append(np.sum([random.randint(-1,1) for k in range(20)]))
group_control = np.array(group_control)
group_test = all_data["test_acc"].values
print("Better than random for classification test:",stat.f_oneway(group_control, group_test))
# Better than random for test_uncertainty
print("--- Better than random for participant uncertainty test  ---")
import random
group_control = []
for i in range(1000):
    group_control.append(np.mean([1-np.abs(random.random()-random.random()) for k in range(12)]))
group_control = np.array(group_control)
group_test = all_data["test_uncert"].values
print("Better than random for uncertainty test:",stat.f_oneway(group_control, group_test))
